# List page layouts

Use layout shells from `@/components/layout`. UI only — do not change API/business logic.

## Which component

| Pattern | Component | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Title + search/toolbar + table (no filters) | `ListPage` | Organizations, Campus |
| Title + **filters inside same card** + toolbar + table | `FilteredListPage` | Grade Setup, Room Details |
| Title + **filters inside same card** + custom body (no AG Grid) | `FilteredPage` | Exam Max Marks, Internal Exam Registration Multi |

```tsx
import { ListPage, FilteredListPage, FilteredPage } from '@/components/layout'
```

## FilteredListPage — filters inside the table card

One card: title (+ filter toggle) → filters → search toolbar → grid → pagination.

```tsx
<FilteredListPage
  title="Room Details"
  filters={
    <CollegeFilterPanel shell="bare" …>
      <Button>Get List</Button>
    </CollegeFilterPanel>
  }
  rowData={rows}
  columnDefs={columnDefs}
  pagination
  toolbar={{ searchPlaceholder: 'Search…' }}
  toolbarTrailing={<Button>Add</Button>}
>
  {/* modals */}
</FilteredListPage>
```

- Do **not** put filters in a separate card above `DataTable`.
- Prefer `CollegeFilterPanel shell="bare"` (or custom filter JSX) so the shell/DataTable owns the card.
- `DataTable` also accepts `filters` directly if you need the slot without the page wrapper.

## ListPage — header + table only

```tsx
<ListPage
  title="Organizations"
  rowData={rows}
  columnDefs={columnDefs}
  pagination
  toolbar={{ searchPlaceholder: 'Search…' }}
  toolbarTrailing={<Button>New</Button>}
/>
```

## Wrong

```tsx
// ❌ Separate filter card + separate table card
<div className="app-card">{/* filters */}</div>
<DataTable title="…" />
```
